      "side": 1,
      "message": "Some observations and questions:\n - Another version of validating JSON config files is this one in Gold https://github.com/google/skia-buildbot/blob/main/golden/go/config/config.go#L141 It uses custom JSON tags to indicate optional fields and doesn\u0027t require embedding a schema, nor an additional third-party dependency.\n - Does this validation system error on fields that included but not a part of the schema? For Gold, it has been useful to include extra fields, e.g. for specifying k8s-specific options in the same JSON file as the runtime configs.\n - Does perf embed its config files? If so, is there a way to validate the configs before the embedding process happens?",
