      "message": "\"Does this validation system error on fields that included but not a part of the schema?\"\n\nYes.\n\n\"For Gold, it has been useful to include extra fields, e.g. for specifying k8s-specific options in the same JSON file as the runtime configs.\"\n\nShouldn\u0027t that also be part of the schema? How would you distinguish between\nthat extra info and a mistake in writing the JSON file?\n\n\"Does perf embed its config files? If so, is there a way to validate the configs before the embedding process happens?\"\n\nThat is part of this CL and happens now every time you run \"go test\":\n\nhttps://skia.googlesource.com/buildbot/+/refs/changes/60/424060/15/perf/go/config/config_test.go#20",
